article.headline: Nebraska 80, Longwood 65
article.story: LINCOLN, Neb. (AP) -- Joe McCray, Aleks Maric and Jamel White each scored 14 points to lead Nebraska to a 80-65 win over Longwood on Friday in the John Thompson Foundation Basketball Challenge. Nebraska (1-0) used 15-3 runs in each half to secure the victory. Nebraska fell behind when Dana Smith hit a long 3-pointer to put the Lancers up 29-26 with 3:40 left in the first half. But the Huskers took advantage of Longwood turnovers and misses to go on its first 15-3 run and take a 41-32 lead at half. Included in the Husker run was McCray's buzzer-beating 3-pointer. The Lancers' Kirk Williams dunked to cut the lead to 58-48 with 11:47 left, but the Huskers went on their next run to put the game away. Nebraska outrebounded Longwood 45-32 and got 12 second-chance points off 17 offensive rebounds. Jason Dourisseau added 13 points for Nebraska. Maurice Sumpter led Longwood (0-1) with 17 points. Bryan Butler had 15 and Dana Smith added 12.
